body:
A loop carried dependency needs to be carried between each iteration so cannot become optional during subgraph execution. The ONNX checker should probably fail the model if it doesn't already. 

If you just want to consume a value, refer to the original name in the outer scope instead of passing it in as a loop carried dependency. See the description and example usage of the outer scope 'a' value in https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/main/docs/Operators.md#loop

I have a graph (body of Loop Node) which returns valid outputs, they are not marked as empty strings.
The only thing I've tried to make an empty is an output of the Loop Node itself (carried dependency from the last step).

And you are right, there is no information in the docs/Operators, that these Loop Node output values could be optional.
But at least, they say that the `cond` could be an optional:
```
cond (optional) : B
A boolean termination condition. Optional. Pass empty string to skip.
```

And if I try to pass an empty string here, I face with the same behavior: InferenceSession just falls silently on initialization.
I attach graph with an optional `cond` and you can run it with the code above.

[loop_optional_cond.onnx.tar.gz](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/7931110/loop_optional_cond.onnx.tar.gz)

Cond is optional as we can default its value to False when running the subgraph. 

I don't believe it's possible to avoid creating the Loop outputs as the spec doesn't allow for them to be optional. As such I don't think your model is valid according to the ONNX spec. If you would like to request an update to the spec please do so via https://github.com/onnx/onnx/issues.

issue.title: Checker should validate the Loop outputs have names.

repository.name: onnx
repository.description: Open standard for machine learning interoperability

issue.body:
# Bug Report

### Describe the bug
An ONNX Runtime user was attempting to create a Loop node where the loop carried dependencies were made optional outputs of the Loop node. i.e. they'd be passed around during loop iteration but not provided as an output of the Loop node. The spec doesn't allow the Loop outputs to be treated as optional, but the ONNX Checker does not fail the node.

### System information
- OS Platform and Distribution (*e.g. Linux Ubuntu 16.04*): Windows 11
- ONNX version (*e.g. 1.7*):  1.10.2
- Python version: 3.9

### Reproduction instructions
Below code will run the checker without it failing. It does have one hack to change the domain of the internal ONNX Runtime LayerNormalization operator which is incorrectly using the ai.onnx domain. This is so the body of the Loop is considered valid

```
import onnx

def change_domain(node, op_type, new_domain):
    if node.op_type == op_type:
        node.domain = new_domain

def iterate_graph_per_node_func(graph, per_node_func, **func_args):
    for node in graph.node:
        per_node_func(node, **func_args)
        # recurse into subgraph for control flow nodes (Scan/Loop/If)
        for attr in node.attribute:
            if attr.HasField('g'):
                iterate_graph_per_node_func(attr.g, per_node_func, **func_args)

model_path = "loop_toy_optional.onnx"

m = onnx.load(model_path)
m.opset_import.append(onnx.helper.make_operatorsetid('com.microsoft', 1))
iterate_graph_per_node_func(m.graph, change_domain, op_type='LayerNormalization', new_domain='com.microsoft')

onnx.checker.check_model(m)

```
- Attach the ONNX model to the issue (where applicable)
See model in https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/10361

### Expected behavior
Checker should require the Loop outputs to have valid names.

body:
I got the point with output carried dependency. 
But now I want to understand if is this true, that I can `Pass empty string to skip.` for `cond`? The spec says that yes, I can do it.
And I did it in my last attached model. The inference fails.

Is there something I'm missing? Or it's just inaccuracy in spec and I should explicitly pass `False` instead of empty string? And why there are no any warnings or errors from the onnxruntime (just silent shut down)

issue.title: Allow for an optional subgraph input to have no type info when running type inferencing

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
Allow for an optional subgraph input to have no type info when running type inferencing
Add a test for a missing optional input to Loop.

**Motivation and Context**
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/10361#issuecomment-1020886432

body: Using an empty string for 'cond' or 'M' should be valid. The Loop implementation handled it, however the type/shape inferencing didn't allow for it, leading to a null reference. Somewhat amazing that in multiple years and many models using Loop that none have ever treated 'cond' or 'M' as optional!

Okay, now it's all clear for me.
I'll make the spec update request to allow optional Loop Node carried outputs.
We can close this one.

Thank you!
